$ iText

{ Download .NET prerequisites

  The following simple → Windows/PowerShell/script[PowerShell script] downloads the necessary → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/DLL[DLLs] to use iText in → Windows/PowerShell.

  gh|about-iText|/lib/download-NuGet-packages.ps1||

}
{ add-types.ps1

 `add-types.ps1` adds the necessary types to a → Windows/PowerShell/session[PowerShell session] so that iText can be used from PowerShell.

  gh|about-iText|/add-types.ps1||

}
{ Hello World

  A simple *Hello World* that creates a PDF document:
  gh|about-iText|/hello-world.ps1||

  Same thing, but with → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/using/namespace[`using namespace`]:
  gh|about-iText|/hello-world-using-namespace.ps1||

}
{ Extract text from a PDF document

  This script extracts text from from a PDF document:
  gh|about-iText|/extract-text.ps1||

}
